{{Infobox building | name = St Georges Hall | alternate_names = St Georges Theatre | status = Partially demolished | image = St Georges Hall facade.jpg | caption=St George's Hall portico fronting Perth's 2008 District Court building | image_alt = | image_size = | map_type = | map_alt = | map_caption = | relief = | altitude = | building_type = Theatre | architectural_style = Grecian | location = | address = 508 [[Hay Street, Perth|Hay Street]] | location_town = [[Perth]] | location_country = Australia | coordinates = {{coord|-31.955189|115.863383|type:landmark_region:AU|format=dms|display=title,inline}} | groundbreaking_date = | start_date = | completion_date = | inauguration_date = 4 December 1879<ref name="inauguration">{{cite news | url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article65956888 | title=St. George's Hall | work=The Inquirer and Commercial News | date=10 December 1879 | accessdate=4 August 2014}}</ref> | renovation_date = | closing_date = | demolition_date = | destruction_date = | floor_count = | seating_type = | seating_capacity = | architect = | architecture_firm = | structural_engineer = | services_engineer = | civil_engineer = | other_designers = | quantity_surveyor = | main_contractor = | awards = | designations = | references = }} '''St Georges Hall''' was a theatre building in [[Perth|Perth, Western Australia]].
==Construction== The hall was constructed in 1879 and was the first dedicated theatre building in Perth.<ref name="heritage-interimentry">{{cite web | url=http://inherit.stateheritage.wa.gov.au/Public/Content/PdfLoader.aspx?id=e4f791b5-6d45-4b88-8093-d9c58c46c24f | title=Interim Entry - St George's Hall Facade | publisher=Heritage Council of Western Australia | work=Register of Heritage Places | accessdate=4 August 2014}}</ref>
==Demolition== The building was demolished in the 1980s with the [[portico]] retained. In 2008 the [[District Court of Western Australia|District Court Building]] was constructed behind the portico.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.districtcourt.wa.gov.au/_files/DCB%20Booklet.pdf | title=The District Court of Western Australia | publisher=District Court of Western Australia | accessdate=4 August 2014 | pages=4}}</ref>
